Sub-Sahara Africa Stocks: CMC Holdings, Sasini, Oceanic Bank

-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 
2011-05-23T16:50:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/sub-sahara-africa-equities-cmc-holdings-of-kenya-sasini-gain-are-active.html
Namibia’s FTSE/ Namibia Overall Index (FTN098) 
fell for the second day, slumping 2 percent at 828.56 by the 4
p.m. close in  Windhoek , the lowest close since March 15.  Kenya ’s All-Share Index tumbled for a second day, losing
0.7 percent to 74.90 by the 3 p.m. close in Nairobi, the lowest
level since April 28. Mauritius’s SEMDEX Index dropped 0.6
percent to 2,085.45 by the 1:30 p.m. close in Port Louis, the
lowest since May 9. The Ghana Stock Exchange Composite Index
rose for a second day, less than 0.1 percent to 1,179.62 by the
3 p.m. end of trading in Accra. The Nigerian Stock Exchange All-
Share Index fell 0.1 percent to 25,762.67 by the 2:30 p.m. in
Lagos, according to an email from the exchange.  The following shares rose or fell in sub-Saharan  Africa ,
excluding  South Africa . Stock symbols are in parentheses.  CMC Holdings Ltd. (CMCH)  , Kenya’s fourth-biggest auto
dealership by sales, fell for the first day in three, losing 5
cents, or 0.5 percent, to 10.6 shillings. Net income declined
0.7 percent to 187.6 million shillings ($2.16 million) in the
six months through March from 188.9 million shillings a year
earlier, the Nairobi-based company reported in a statement in
the Daily Nation newspaper today.  Oceanic Bank International Plc (OCEANIC)  , a Nigerian
lender bailed out by the central bank two years ago, rose for
the first time in three days, climbing 9 kobo, or 4.7 percent,
to 1.99 naira, after Global Fleet Group said it bought Oceanic’s
unit in Sao Tome and Principe.  Sasini Ltd. (STCL)  , a Kenyan tea and coffee producer,
surged 50 cents, or 4.6 percent, to 11.40 shillings, the highest
close since Feb. 28. The company’s first-half profit increased
39 percent to 423.5 million shillings, it said in a statement
published in the Daily Nation newspaper today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
